title: Warren Hills field hockey edges Voorhees on strokes in county semifinal
text:

Warren Hills 2, Voorhees 1 -- Rapid recap 
Warren Hills Regional High School's field hockey team defeated Voorhees 2-1 on penalty strokes Saturday morning in a Hunterdon/Warren/Sussex semifinal in Lebanon Township. 
Turning point : Trailing 1-0, Warren Hills' Rebecca Sigman scored to tie it with 10:18 left in regulation. The Blue Streaks seemed to have the upper hand from there. 
Top performer s: Warren Hills goalkeeper Jackie de Raismes opens the penalty stroke session with a save on Voorhees senior star Kathryn Roncoroni . Dani Profita then knocked home the winning shot in the fourth round. 
What it means : These teams have had many epic battles over the years and this one was certainly no exception. Warren Hills advances to next Saturday's H//W/S final against Hunterdon Central at Hackettstown. It was a very tough loss for Voorhees, but the Vikings will be heard from in the state playoffs.
